1444313 20 Insertion of new sections 36A to 36D.- After section 36 of the principal Act, the following sections shall be inserted, namely:- " 36A. Declaration and management of a conservation reserve.- (1) The State Government may, after having consultations with the local communities, declare any area owned by the Government, particularly the areas adjacent to National Parks and sanctuaries a d those areas which link one protected area with another, as a conservation reserve for protecting landscapes, seascapes, flora and fauna and their habitat:
Provided that where the conservation reserve includes any land owned by the Central Government, its prior concurrence shall be obtained before making such declaration.
1503977 2The provisions of sub- section (2) of section 18, sub- sections (2), (3) and (4) of section 27, sections 30, 32 and clauses (b) and (c) of section 33 shall, as far as may be, apply in relation to a conservation reserve as they apply in relation to a sa ctuary.
24602 36B Conservation reserve management committee.-
646362 1The State Government shall constitute a conservation reserve management committee to advise the Chief Wild Life Warden to conserve, manage and maintain the conservation reserve.
9389 2The committee shall consist of a representative of the forest or Wild Life Department, who shall be the Member- Secretary of the Committee, one representative of each Village Panchayat in whose jurisdiction the reserve is located, three representative of non- governmental organisations working in the field of wild life conservation and one representative each from the Department of Agriculture and Animal Husbandry.
1695426 3The Committee shall regulate its own procedure including the quorum.
1112040 36C Declaration and management of community reserve.-
871040 1The State Government may, where the community or an individual has volunteered to conserve wild life and its habitat, declare any private or community land not comprised within a National Park, sa ctuary or a conservation reserve, as a community reserve, for protecting fauna, flora and traditional or cultural conservation values and practices.
994439 2The provisions of sub- section (2) of section 18, sub- sections (2), (3) and (4) of section 27, sections 30, 32 and clauses (b) and (c) of section 33 shall, as far as may be, apply in relation to a community reserve as they apply in relation to a sanct ary.
1962183 3After the issue of notification under sub- section (1), no change in the land use pattern shall be made within the community reserve, except in accordance with a resolution passed by the management committee and approval of the same by the State Gover ment.
1248202 36D Community reserve management committee.-
1029023 1The State Government shall constitute a Community Reserve management committee, which shall be the authority responsible for conserving, maintaining and managing the community reserve.
1689029 2The committee shall consist of five representatives nominated by the Village Panchayat or where such Panchayat does not exist by the members of the Gram Sabha and one representative of the State Forests or Wild Life Department under whose jurisdictio the community reserve is located.
486693 3The committee shall be the competent authority to prepare and implement the management plan for the community reserve and to take steps to ensure the protection of wild life and its habitat in the reserve.
1788834 4The committee shall elect a Chairman who shall also be the Honorary Wild Life Warden on the community reserve.
25955 5The committee shall regulate its own procedure including the quorum.".
